## Description
This room covers the key metrics used to measure SOC effectiveness and team performance. It introduces SLA, MTTD, MTTA, and MTTR, explains the importance of the False Positive rate, and covers how L1 analysts can actively contribute to improving these metrics. Completed through conceptual and reading-based exercises.

## Key Concepts Covered
- SLA (Service Level Agreement) — response time commitments governing SOC operations
- MTTD (Mean Time to Detect) — how quickly threats are identified
- MTTA (Mean Time to Acknowledge) — how fast analysts acknowledge alerts
- MTTR (Mean Time to Respond/Resolve) — time taken to contain and resolve incidents
- False Positive rate — impact on analyst workload and detection quality
- Improving metrics as an L1 analyst — Tier 1 contributions to team performance
- SOC team performance management framework

## SOC Analyst Takeaways
- SLA Awareness: Time-based commitments that govern alert handling speed
- Detection Quality: MTTD and False Positive rate reflect health of detection rules
- Response Efficiency: MTTA and MTTR identify bottlenecks and measure response speed
- L1 Contribution: Tier 1 analysts directly influence team metrics through accurate triage

## Skills Demonstrated
- Interpretation of core SOC performance metrics (SLA, MTTD, MTTA, MTTR)
- Awareness of False Positive rate and its operational impact
- Understanding of how L1 behavior influences team performance outcomes
- Conceptual application of metrics to evaluate SOC effectiveness

